Guard ggml_backend_load_all_from_path behind GGML_BACKEND_DL.

When GGML_BACKEND_DL=OFF (Linux, macOS, Windows) the backends are
statically linked and there are no .so files to dlopen. Without this
guard ggml still walks the executable directory and system paths looking
for libggml-*.so / libqvac-diffusion-ggml-*.so files, which is both
wasteful and risks loading an incompatible system-installed library.

ggml-base already receives a PUBLIC compile definition GGML_BACKEND_DL
when the cmake option is ON (ggml/src/CMakeLists.txt line 217), so the
preprocessor symbol is available in ggml-backend-reg.cpp without any
additional cmake change.

--- a/ggml/src/ggml-backend-reg.cpp
+++ b/ggml/src/ggml-backend-reg.cpp
@@ -539,6 +539,7 @@ void ggml_backend_load_all() {
 
 void ggml_backend_load_all_from_path(const char * dir_path) {
+#ifdef GGML_BACKEND_DL
 #ifdef NDEBUG
     bool silent = true;
 #else
@@ -558,4 +559,7 @@ void ggml_backend_load_all_from_path(const char * dir_path) {
     if (backend_path) {
         ggml_backend_load(backend_path);
     }
+#else
+    (void)dir_path;
+#endif // GGML_BACKEND_DL
 }
